<TITLE> Villa hopes for thumbs up over finger injury </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEUSTIFT, June 11 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Spain striker David Villa, the first player to score a hat-trick at Euro 2008, sustained a bizarre injury to his finger while celebrating his first goal in the 4-1 win over Russia on Tuesday. The 26-year-old, who trained with a bandaged finger on his right hand on Wednesday, suffered the injury after running over to hug team mate Fernando Torres who had set him up to score. "I got my finger caught in Fernando's shirt when we were celebrating the goal and bent it back," Villa told a news conference. "It hurts quite a bit, but it is nothing important." The Spanish press officer said the striker would have a routine x-ray to confirm there was no serious damage
